[zero_shot][olmo3_7b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 99/200 done id=gsm8k_test_601 prediction='Let\'s break down the number of games Steve gets each year.\n\n**Year 1 (Birthday only):**\n- He receives a console (not a game) and 5 games for his birthday.\n- He does not mention any games from Christmas in the first year, but the problem says he gets 5 games for Christmas "every year." However, since the question starts with his birthday gifts and the description is general, let\'s assume the first Christmas is after the first year. But the wording says "for his birthday" and "for Christmas every year," so in the first year, only the birthday games are specified. The problem likely intends that the Christmas gifts start from the second year onward, but since it says "every year," let\'s check both interpretations. However, the most straightforward reading is that the 5 games for Christmas are received each year, including the first. But the problem says "his parents get him a console along with 5 games for his birthday" — and then "he also gets 5 games for Christmas every year." So, every year includes both a birthday set of 5 games and a Christmas set of 5 games, unless otherwise stated. But the question says "for Christmas every year," which could mean starting from the first' gold='104' correct=False
