[zero_shot][olmo3_7b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 100/200 done id=gsm8k_test_611 prediction='Step 1: Determine the total duration of the research.  \nThe initial funding covered the first 5 months. The research took 10 times as long as the initial period, so total duration = 5 × 10 = 50 months.\n\nStep 2: Calculate the cost for the first 5 months.  \nThis is given as $100,000 for the first 5 months.\n\nStep 3: Find the funding per month for the first 5 months.  \n$100,000 over 5 months = $100,000 ÷ 5 = $20,000 per month for the first 5 months.\n\nStep 4: Determine the funding rate for months beyond the first 5.  \nAfter the first 5 months, each month costs 50% more than before.  \n50% of $20,000 = $20,000 × 0.5 = $10,000.  \nSo, new monthly funding = $20,000 + $10,000 = $30,000 per month.\n\nStep5: Calculate the number of months beyond the initial 5.  \nTotal months = 50.  \nMonths after initial = 50 − 5 = 45 months.\n\nStep6: Compute the cost for the 45' gold='1450000' correct=False
