[zero_shot][olmo3_7b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 110/200 done id=gsm8k_test_696 prediction='Let\'s break down the problem step by step.\n\n**Step 1: Find Betty\'s points.**  \nAdam has 50 points.  \nBetty collected 30% more than Adam.  \n30% of 50 is 0.3 × 50 = 15.  \nSo Betty has 50 + 15 = **65 points**.\n\n**Step 2: Find Tom\'s points.**  \nTom has 30 points less than Betty.  \nBetty has 65, so Tom has 65 - 30 = **35 points**.\n\n**Step 3: Find Marta\'s points.**  \nMarta collected 3 times more points than Tom.  \nThis means Marta has 3 × Tom\'s points.  \nIs "3 times more" means 3 × Tom\'s points, or 4 × (Tom\'s + 3×Tom)?  \nIn most math problems, "3 times more" means 3 × Tom\'s points.  \nSo Marta has 3 × 35 = **105 points**.\n\n**Step 4: Find the total class points.**  \nAdd up all the points:  \nAdam: 50  \nBetty: 65  \nTom: 35  \nMarta: 105' gold='145' correct=False
