[zero_shot][olmo3_7b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 126/200 done id=gsm8k_test_810 prediction='Let\'s break down the problem step by step.\n\n1. **Initial condition:**  \n   At the beginning of the year, there are 10 students.\n\n2. **Growth pattern:**  \n   Every month, the number of students doubles at the end of the month.  \n   We are to find the total number of *additional* students by the end of May compared to the start of the year.\n\n3. **Time span:**  \n   From the start of the year to the end of May is 6 months (January, February, March, April, May ends — that\'s 5 months after the start, but since doubling happens at the END of each month, we need to consider the state at the END of May for the total count).\n\n   However, the question asks:  \n   *"how many additional students would have joined by the end of May, above and beyond the number already on campus at the beginning of the year?"*\n\n   So, we need the number of students at the END of May, minus the initial 10 students.\n\n4. **Calculate the number at the end of each month:**\n   - **End of January:**  \n     Start: 10  \n     After doubling: 10 × 2 = 20' gold='310' correct=False
