[zero_shot][olmo3_7b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 198/200 done id=gsm8k_test_1310 prediction='Let’s break down the problem step by step.\n\n1. **Determine how far Aaron ran.**  \n   The problem says Vanessa ran 4 miles, and Vanessa ran only half as far as Aaron (since "Vanessa ran twice as far as Aaron did" is misread; actually, "Vanessa ran 4 miles, and Aaron ran half that distance because Vanessa ran twice as far as Aaron").  \n   Let A = distance Aaron ran.  \n   Vanessa ran twice as far as Aaron:  \n   \\( 2A = 4 \\) miles  \n   So, \\( A = \\frac{4}{2} = 2 \\) miles.  \n   Aaron ran 2 miles.\n\n2. **Find Aaron’s speed.**  \n   Aaron completed 2 miles in 16 minutes.  \n   Speed = distance / time = \\( \\frac{2 \\text{ miles}}{16 \\text{ minutes}} = \\frac{1}{8} \\) miles per minute.\n\n   But we can also relate their mile speeds. Let’s define:  \n   Let \\( v_V \\) = Vanessa’s speed (miles per minute)  \n   Let \\( v_A \\) = Aaron’s speed  \n   Given: Aaron runs each mile twice' gold='64' correct=False
