[zero_shot][olmo3_7b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 199/200 done id=gsm8k_test_1312 prediction='Step 1: Determine the number of reservations per week.  \nThe restaurant is open 2 days a week and gets 6 reservations each night.  \nSo, total reservations per week = 6 reservations/night × 2 nights = 12 reservations.\n\nStep 2: Calculate the number of meals ordered per week.  \nEach reservation corresponds to 2 meals ordered.  \nTotal meals per night = 2 reservations × 2 meals/reservation = 4 meals.  \nTotal meals per week = 4 meals/night × 2 nights = 8 meals.\n\nStep 3: Calculate the cost of meals per reservation.  \nEach meal costs $5, so for 2 meals per reservation:  \nCost per reservation (meals) = 2 meals × $5/meal = $10.\n\nStep4: Calculate the total revenue from meals per week.  \nTotal meals per week = 8 meals.  \nRevenue from meals = 8 meals × $5/meal = $40.\n\nStep5: Add the cost of wine per week.  \nThey order 1 bottle of wine per night at $5 per bottle.  \nWine revenue per week = 2 nights × $5 = $10.\n\nStep6: Find the total weekly revenue.' gold='180' correct=False
